Abu Dhabi – Abu Dhabi National Oil Company (ADNOC) on Monday, signed a strategic framework agreement with Italy’s energy company Eni, for collaboration in carbon capture, utilisation, and storage (CCUS), the official news agency WAM reported. According to the agreement, ADNOC and Eni will jointly explore opportunities for collaboration in innovative geomechanical workflows for CCUS programme as well as in advanced analysis and modelling of thermally-induced fractures in oil and gas reservoirs. They also reviewed opportunities in the field of research and development across the oil and gas value chain. (Xinhua/NAN)